  "content": "# Phone Readability Font Scale for 1080px Canvas\n\nLinkedIn carousel canvas is 1080px wide. On a phone (~375px viewport), content scales to ~0.35x.\n\n| Role | CSS Size | On Phone | Readable? |\n|------|----------|----------|-----------|\n| Cover title | 68px | ~24px | Yes |\n| Slide title | 58px | ~20px | Yes |\n| Subtitle | 28px | ~10px | Minimum |\n| Body | 20-24px | ~7-8px | Limit |\n| Secondary | 18px | ~6px | Labels only |\n| Metadata | 15-16px | ~5px | Borderline |\n\n**Minimum readable: 15px.** Never go below.\n\n**Critical lesson:** Never adjust all font sizes at once for \"phone readability\" — this kills visual hierarchy. Always adjust by role while maintaining >= 1.3x ratio between adjacent levels (e.g. title/subtitle, subtitle/body).",
